< review>
Eating here while traveling on an 18 hour drive was the best choice of the trip. The two gentlemen work were cheerful and helpful. My wife and be indecisive and he helped her get everything she wanted by putting items on the side and offering samples. We were the only ones in the restaurant for a short time and the two staff were talking to each other and seemed to genuinely be enjoyable people. The food was good. We had teriyaki, spicy chicken, and orange chicken. All was well cooked and tasted good. Environment, staff, and food made for an awesome afternoon stop.</review>

<rating>3</rating>< Review>
I go here every so often but as far as Chicken Bowls go, it's far from the best I've had. If you're in the area though and want something healthy like a Chicken Bowl then it's not terrible.

My biggest complaint is the Chicken itself, it's completely overcooked and tough/rubbery and while your choice of sauce covers up some of the dryness of the chicken, you definitely still notice how tough and overcooked it is, the flavor is fine though. Pricing is average, $8-$10 and portion size is good, I usually get the regular size and it's enough to fill me up.

Edit: In response to the owners response:

I just got the regular Spicy Chicken Bowl, I didn't specify chicken breast option but I'm pretty sure I had breast meat, not difficult to discern white meat from dark especially in texture.

I appreciate the response, I'll mention it to the manager next time I'm in about my experience.</Review>

<rating>5</rating>< Review>
Best sandwiches on the coast. Great owners and staff, amazing vibes. Everything is as local as they can be. I might be biased because I live here, but I love the Elk Store and recommend it to anyone who is driving by!

Pro tip: if you want a sandwich and your in a rush, call ahead and order one. They take their time at the Elk Store, every sandwich is hand crafted with love. You will find the time they take in every aspect of the store results in high quality all around.</Review>

< name>
Owen Freeman< /name>
< text>
We did a coastal riding trip to Fort Bragg and knew we needed to stop based on the previous reviews. We grabbed a custom sandwich - smoked turkey on sourdough and some of the pasta salad (and a huge jug of water for our trip) and headed down the road to glass beach.
The sandwich was good. I will give it 4.5 stars. The staff was great. So why the 5 star rating?The overall experience was great. But the stand out was the pasta salad. They should sell this stuff by the bucket loads.
OMG! Best pasta salad I‚Äôve ever had. My only complaint is the little portion is a tease. I want a bigger portion after tasting it. I almost went back the 50 miles for more.
The ginger cookie was really good too.
Overall, it‚Äôs worth a stop. Eat there or take for a near by picnic - I would recommend this as a good stop on the HWY 1, in either direction.<//text>

An amazing place!  If you ever rent a home nearby, you don't need to bring any food, just load up here.  Excellent, smart high quality selection (what small store in a dinky town is going to have fresh miso?!)  Helpful and cheerful people run this place and make amazing sandwiches and other fresh food daily....plus deliveries from all sorts of great vendors from bread to coffee to eggs to cheese. < review>
The Elk Store is a must stop if you are passing through the lovely town of Elk. The quality in selection of products offered here is incredibly impressive! Everything from local ciders and beers, wines, and gifts, to a delicious deli counter with the best sandwiches on the coast(even gluten free options)! A lot of their products are organic, and you can tell that the owners put a lot of time into vetting and deciding what products to sell. The staff are also super friendly, and accomodating. One of the best gems in Elk!< /review>

<rate>5</rate><review>Not much along the north coast CA 1 but this is worth stopping at.  We arrived about 30 minutes before they opened, but my wife really wanted a sandwich for lunch so we hung out at the beach til they opened.  I'm glad we did.  The two people working were very friendly and helpful with answering any questions and with suggestions.  They carry a lot of great beer, local wine, and organic products.  The sandwiches are very reasonably priced, especially considering how isolated they are.  We grabbed 2 of their signature sandwiches, some local products, and a beer.  When we stopped on the beach about 2 hours later the sandwiches hadn't gotten soggy and were still fresh.  Both were pretty hearty and very good. <gmapID>0x808100d708fb1465:0x8242cdd9adaa1a54</gmapID></record></dataset><record>
<Response>None</Response><gmap_id>0x808100d708fb1465:0x8242cdd9adaa1a54<//gmap_id>< Review>
Stopped in this past Saturday around 1 pm. First thing I notice is a sign in the door that says we welcome all religions, races, etc. you are safe here. Ok good to know, got the warm and fuzzy feelings already. No one greeted us as we walked in but the store was cute and had a good variety of food etc..  I picked up a couple of items and then stood in front of the deli case and waited to have my order taken. After a few minutes I turned around and when I turned back around the girl behind the deli counter had started taken another person's order. This person actually stepped in front of me to give her his order. Ok, fine. I was skipped but maybe it was my fault for turning around. I waited again for a few minutes to have my order taken. A group of about 4-5 walked in and we are all waiting to have our orders taken. Another girl walks behind the deli counter and has a conversation with the worker who has been manning the deli. She turns around and completely skips over me and begins speaking to the group who had walked in after I did. I've now been completely ignored twice at the deli and at this point I drop everything in my hands on the counter and walked out. I wasted 15 minutes of an otherwise beautiful day in this place and was left with such a bad taste in my mouth after having been treated as invisible by the people who work here. Fortunately for me, there were lots of other places in the area where I was given great customer service.</Review>

<user_id>115737756066712270687<//user_id>< name>
Gregory Lee Parks</name>
< time>
1621380750131<//time>
<rate>5< /rate>< Review>
Comfortably between dive bar and family restaurant, this pub's authenticity comes from a distinct lack trying too hard. Decent enough drinks, including cider. Decent enough food including enough English staples to call themselves a pub.

There is nothing fancy about this place, but it is humble and comfortable enough to keep me coming back.

There are just a few TVs for sports, nice amount of outdoor and indoor seating, and a digital juke box if you want to change the music.

So long as you aren't looking for fancy, I highly recommend this place for both food and drinks.< /Review>

< userid>
108211534054810104269<//userid>
<name>Enrique Torres<//name>< time>
1510616062299<//time>
<rating>5</rating>< review>
An Englishman, a Scot and a Yorkshireman walk into a pub...

...and we all had a great time.

The Duke of Edinburgh is proper English pub across from the new Apple spaceship HQ. It looks a bit tatty from the outside--at the end of an old strip mall--but feels like an English pub on the inside. Not just because the interior looks like it was brought over from the Home Counties and then well used for quarter of a century. But because of the great English food and friendly service. And it's not forced American theme pub "Have a nice day!" friendliness from the staff. It's an easy chattiness with some blokeish banter. It felt like being back home in Manchester.

We all ordered fish and chips, with Icelandic cod. Fresh and delicious. Plus Boddingtons and Old Speckled Hen: Lovely creamy bitter ales.

The Yorkshireman liked the ale. The Englishman loved the fish and chips. And Scotsman didn't complain about the prices. That's no joke; that's high praise.</review>

115406449322051069557< /userid>
< name>
Mizumi Tenji< /name>
< Time>
1544932220071<//Time>
< Rate>
3</Rate>
< Text>
I bought a specialty dish that cost $26 - Grilled Salmon. Imagine a small filet, if that, next to a pool of peas, a couple of bits of broccoli, cucumber and one piece of cauliflower.

That's it. I'm glad I ordered an extra salad ($6... You can imagine how I felt paying $32 for the meal I just described).

Compare that to my partner's dish, $17 - Cornish Pasty. It's buttery, crumbly, sizeable and has relatively moist minced meat inside. He poured some turkey gravy on it to make it stand out more and it sure did!

The three stars comes from the fact that, so far, the more expensive, the less you get. My tip for you is to stay simple. $11-$20 dishes seem to be a sweet spot.

I'll come back again to try their drinks, next time. I hear Mai Tai's are $10!<//Text>

116636761363964182154< /user>
< Review>
Update February 2018:

Oh no!
New owners and new management. They jacked their prices WAY up. Weekend lunch is now $26.99 (used to be $19.99).
Plus they now charge $2 extra if you want to add avocado, or use soy paper instead of seaweed. And my favorite roll was gone!

But the saddest part was the quality of the fish. Some was dried out and flavorless, like it had been sitting around for too long. Others tasted fishy.... The bad kind of fishy. If you are used to eating at good sushi restaurants, you'll know what I mean. So, with the significant rise in price, along with the definite drop in quality, we will not be back. We will sadly be mourning the loss of our favorite sushi joint. :(

Original review...
August 2017:
Far and away our favorite GoTo Sushi stop. Authentic sushi chefs, always top quality, top notch service, and the all you can eat is an excellent value at $20 for lunch. My favorite is the Hawaiian roll, and my husband orders different items each time. We eat here a couple times a month.</Review>

<user>105884975127078909181<//user>< name>
Steve Hillery< /name>
< Date>
1536388097634< /Date>
<rate>3< /rate><Text>First visit was for dinner, decided to play it safe and ordered the Bento Box with four slices of mixed sushi, 8 pieces of California Roll, 8 pieces of Spicy Tuna Roll, House Salad, Miso Soup, and steamed rice for $15.
The soup was nothing special being overly salty to my taste, while being skimpy on the Miso. The salad, on the other hand, was quite good. Very fresh, delicious, slightly sweet dressing. The dried cranberries added a little extra kick. The sushi was average. Fairly small slices that while fairly fresh, lacked the firmness and delicate aroma of the best sushi I've had. The California roll was primarily just immigration crab wrapped in kelp and rice. Same with the Spicy Tuna Roll. While good, I missed the variety of tastes I've experienced in other rolls that included additional ingredients such as spears of avocado, cucumber, and lemon grass, for example. Rice was fine. Slightly sticky and nice and steamy. Way I like it.
Price was more than fair for what I got in quantity. I gave up when I finally got to the Spicy Tuna Rolls. Took those home and enjoyed them later that evening.
As for the environment, it was just OK. I noticed when entering that the front door glass had not been cleaned in a while as it was full of smudges and fingerprints. Not a good first impression. Reminded me of going into a fast food joint rather than a Japanese Restaurant. However, once inside things were adequately clean.
Service was OK. Everyone just quietly served the table. No small talk, or effort to add to the occasion. Chefs were all Asian, with requesite black smocks and rising sun headbands.
All in all, an OK place to go.</Text><Pics>None<//Pics>< Resp>

< text>
After a handful of subpar experiences with mechanics in Chico, I still found myself looking for the right place to go. A friend of mine, whose family has been in the BMW motorcycle business for generations, recommended I see Jeff at A&T Auto Care.

I brought my car in for a nasty front wheel issue. I didn't even know just how serious it was. I was explained the issues clearly, and when another problem was found later they insisted on picking me up and driving me there so I can see it firsthand and ask any questions I had. Now my car rides smoother than I ever thought it could. It's like driving on air! Above all, they made sure my family is safe. I'm blown away.

Friendly, professional, and honest. All I can ask for in a mechanic shop. Thanks everyone, I'll be back!<//text>

They tried to find ways to charge me more. It did not feel right when I was charged $55 at first only to tell me that my car was not ready for the Smog because it looks like someone worked on my car recently and disconnected the battery. The last car maintennance I had and the last people who touched my Honda car were last month with the Honda Dealership itself, so I asked them about it and they said they did not even touch nor disconnected anything. Then, the guy at the front desk told me to drive my car 40 more miles and go back to them with $20 to get the certificate. I came back and was asked if I drove 40 miles and I said more than that because I work every day and drive about a total of 40 minutes each day to work and back. Then, they said my car was still not ready and asked if they could just drive my car around so I let them. The guy who drove my car came back and said it's finally ready but he only drove 2 miles. Seriously?? That's already a total of more than 50 miles total this week since they asked me to drive 40. I was charged about $28 with a total of $83 to pass my car for Smog. It looks and feels like people in the business are taking advantage of this COVID situation. They were NOT even wearing a mask when they are supposed to, NO sign stating everyone must be 6 ft apart, NO sanitizers, NO other signs that the Corona Virus, per state, policies are being enforced, and the chairs inside where the customers sit are next to each other without space. I would hate to have this business closed down for not enforcing health protocols, so Im not coming back to this place instead and write a review to give a heads up to those citizens who care about the situation. If you don't care, then this review is not for you.<//text>

<user_id>112538517004023109514</user_id><username>PERRY DINH</username><Time>1512543044171< /Time>< rating>
1<//rating>
< review>
The food is good and most of the people who work here are nice. However the older gentleman with the cap who seems to be in charge is rude, a coward, and a racist. He messed up my order and when I politely asked him to correct it, he threw the plate down to the side and called me a racial slur for Chinese people in Spanish to one of his other co workers. Unfortunately I don't think he realized that even though I was Asian, I can still speak and understand Spanish. Funny how when you pretend not to speak a language how much you can ascertain about people's true natures. Ironic too, as with him being a minority himself, he should have understood and respected other races better. As a man, if he had a problem with me, he should have said it to my face instead of calling me something he's thought I didn't understand to one of his co workers.
In the end, I stayed calm, smiled at him, kept a close eye on him as he cooked my food and ultimately got my new plate, as I had already waited too long in line to just give him the satisfaction of storming off. However it will be my last time going here. From reading other reviews below, it seems as though I'm not the only one who feels this way about the service here. I would suggest everyone else try Pepe's Mexican food as an alternative. As a veteran who has fought for this country, I feel deeply let down that I come home to a country where I am racially prejudiced against (ironically by someone who speaks even less english than me lol)< /review>

< text>
I have been eating at Boca for over 30+ years. The food, the service and many of the people have been the same the whole time. Although I frequent all of the locations over the years. The original location on Hacienda is my favorite. Easy menu consistent food is what keeps me coming back. When they say dont judge a book by its cover, Boca is what they are talking about!! The prices they are amazing $2.75 for a taco special, this includes avacado and sour cream...WOW...you wont get this anywhere else. Lastly dont let the line discourage you,  its worth the wait, besides it gives you a chance to make up your mind.  Seriously though the line moves pretty quickly!!</text>
